transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Good morning. Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: I was online a couple of months ago, and we were messing around.

Speaker 1: We saw that score blue thing, whatever it's called.

Speaker 2: I tried to fill it out, and we decided to cancel it, and we did.

Speaker 1: And all of a sudden, in December, I get a receipt from you guys for 10 pills.

Speaker 2: That's $63.

Speaker 1: Okay. I can help you out.

Speaker 2: And then I get another one the other day.

Speaker 1: It says recurring prescription.

Speaker 2: I didn't recur it. I canceled the whole thing.

Speaker 1: I didn't even finish filling out the end of it.

Speaker 2: Okay. I can help you out. Nick, can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 1: 08-1956.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much. I see your VIP status.

Speaker 1: Yeah, it looks like you signed up on December 19th.

Speaker 2: And we didn't even finish filling the whole form out, and we said,

Speaker 1: let's cancel it.

Speaker 2: And a month later, I get a thing in the mail with 10 little pills.

Speaker 1: Okay. Well, yeah, if you don't, then what you can do,

Speaker 2: I can go ahead and cancel you out,

Speaker 1: and then you just have to return those two bottles,

Speaker 2: and then we can get your money back.

Speaker 1: No, I have to mail this back to you.

Speaker 2: You just can't cancel it right now and reverse the charges on it?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Or do I have to call the bank and have them reverse it?

Speaker 1: Well, I canceled you out, but you received the product,

Speaker 2: so we need that back in order for a refund.

Speaker 1: We can't just give you a free product and issue you a refund.

Speaker 2: So if you just write return to sender on the – do you have the envelope still?

Speaker 1: I don't know.

Speaker 2: I'm not sure what I do.

Speaker 1: I think it's in the bedroom someplace.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: If you have that envelope, you can just put both those bottles in there,

Speaker 2: tape it up, and write return to sender.

Speaker 1: That way you don't have to pay for postage,

Speaker 2: and there's already a tracking number on there.

Speaker 1: Why would they put a recurring subscription, a monthly subscription?

Speaker 2: I never even checked that box.

Speaker 1: Yeah, a quantity of 10, the doctor just puts you on automatic refills,

Speaker 2: which you don't have to do.

Speaker 1: A lot of people just like to go ahead and put a six-month pause on that.

Speaker 2: That way it keeps your prescription active and allows you to call in for a refill.

Speaker 1: Nick, how is the medication working out for you?

Speaker 2: I took one pill and it wasn't any difference.

Speaker 1: I didn't have a problem.

Speaker 2: We're just messing around.

Speaker 1: Let's try this Scor-Blue shit, see how it's advertising all over the place.

Speaker 2: Do you have the pills on you right now?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I do.

Speaker 2: Can you tell me what's imprinted on the individual pill?

Speaker 1: Oh, man.

Speaker 2: The pill's not even blue.

Speaker 1: No, it's not going to be blue.

Speaker 2: It will be white.

Speaker 1: But I want to know if it says AC on there.

Speaker 2: What does that mean?

Speaker 1: If it says AC, that means it's generic.

Speaker 2: They sent you the wrong ones.

Speaker 1: That's what I'm trying to find out.

Speaker 2: For $47 they sent me the wrong one?

Speaker 1: On the individual pill, what's imprinted on it?

Speaker 2: There's nothing imprinted on it.

Speaker 1: It doesn't say AC, 390 or 340?

Speaker 2: Hold on, let me get my magnifying glass out.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: Take your time.

Speaker 1: Hold on.

Speaker 2: This is AC 34.

Speaker 1: Yeah, okay, that's what I thought.

Speaker 2: Yeah, the pharmacy sent you actually just regular generic Viagra.

Speaker 1: You did not receive the AGB.

Speaker 2: Give me a second.

Speaker 1: I'm going to get you out a replacement, and then I'm going to tell you how you—

Speaker 2: I don't want a replacement.

Speaker 1: I want it canceled.

Speaker 2: Okay, well, I went ahead and canceled you out.

Speaker 1: So the address is actually on the bottle.

Speaker 2: It's Go-Go Meds 525 Alexandria Pike in Southgate, Kentucky.

Speaker 1: So if you just ship it back to there, then we can go ahead and issue those two refunds.

Speaker 2: So I have to spend money to send it back to you?

Speaker 1: Yeah, we don't send return labels.

Speaker 2: Well, why would they do that?

Speaker 1: In the first place, they sent me the wrong pill.
